A benefits cheat who claimed he was so disabled that he could not turn over in bed was caught out after officials spotted him playing in the local football league.

Pete Iron pocketed more than £48,000 after telling welfare officers that he could only walk with a stick for 40 yards and fell frequently.

But undercover investigators filmed the  43-year-old – nicknamed Pistol Pete – putting in  energetic performances as the star midfielder  for Sunday league team Solent Lions FC.

