Prosecutor Rob Griffiths said Iron had claimed disability living allowance with a care component and mobility allowance.

Barry McElduff, defending, said Iron's GP confirmed his condition warranted the benefit when he first started claiming in 2000.

He admitted it later improved but said it had eased only to a point where his client would have still been entitled to a lower level of benefit.

